                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No American record of this conversation has been found. According to Pickersgill,
                    p. 510, from which the information set forth above has been derived, this
                    conversation followed a dinner at the White House attended by Roosevelt,
                    Churchill, Mackenzie King, and several other unnamed guests. During the
                    conversation, peacemaking and postwar international organizations were
                    discussed, and Roosevelt set forth his proposal for a Supreme Council of the
                    United Nations.</p>
            </div>
